        <name>(not in quiz) 37.2.3.11 Seven batches of articles are manufactured</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;p class="HELM_exercise"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Seven batches of articles are manufactured. Each batch contains {@n_art_each_batch@} articles. Each article has, independently, a probability of {@p_art_being_def@} of being defective. Find the probability that there is at least one defective article:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol class="HELM_parts"&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;In exactly 4 of the batches [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;In 4 or more of the batches [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Note:&lt;/b&gt; round your answer up to \(4\) decimal places.&lt;/p&gt;</questiontext>
        <questiontextformat>1</questiontextformat>
        <generalfeedback>&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;SOLUTION:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;First, let's compute the probability of having at least 1 defective article on each batch:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Let \(Z\) be the number of defective articles in a batch, this follows a binomial distribution with \(n={@n_art_each_batch@}\) and \(p = {@p_art_being_def@} \)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\(\begin{align} \text{P}(Z \geq 1) &amp;amp; = 1 - \text{P}(Z &amp;lt; 1) = 1 - \text{P}(Z=0) \\ &amp;amp; = 1 - \ ^{@n_art_each_batch@}\!C_0p^0(1-p)^{{@n_art_each_batch@}} = 1 - (1 - {@p_art_being_def@})^{{@n_art_each_batch@}} \approx {@p_batch@}&amp;nbsp;\end{align}&amp;nbsp;\)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;With the latter result, we can compute now what the exercise is asking us. Let \(X\) be the number of batches with at least one defective article, so \(X\) follows a binomial distribution with \(n = 7\) and \(p = {@p_batch@}\):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol class="HELM_parts"&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;\(\text{P} (X=4) =&amp;nbsp;\ ^7\!C_4({@p_batch@})^4(1-{{@p_batch@}})^3 = {@ta_1@}&amp;nbsp; \)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;\(\begin{align} \text{P} (X\geq 4)&amp;nbsp; = &amp;amp; \ ^7\!C_4({@p_batch@})^4(1-{{@p_batch@}})^3 +&amp;nbsp;^7\!C_5({@p_batch@})^5(1-{{@p_batch@}})^2 \\ &amp;amp; +&amp;nbsp;^7\!C_6({@p_batch@})^6(1-{{@p_batch@}}) +&amp;nbsp;^7\!C_7({@p_batch@})^7&amp;nbsp;= {@ta_2@}&amp;nbsp;\end{align} \)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;/ol&gt;</generalfeedback>
